ster","line":74},{"title":"Author/Marc Stadler","target":"Author/Marc Stadler","line":75},{"title":"Author/Marc Stadler","target":"Author/Marc Stadler","line":76},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/wittstein_corallocins_2016/wittstein_corallocins_2016.pdf","line":78}],"metadata":{"id":"wittstein_corallocins_2016","type":"article-journal","title":"Corallocins A-C, Nerve Growth and Brain-Derived Neurotrophic Factor Inducing Metabolites from the Mushroom Hericium coralloides.","issued":{"date-parts":[[2016]]},"DOI":"10.1021/acs.jnatprod.6b00371","container-title":"Journal of Natural Products","abstract":"Three new natural products, corallocins A–C (1–3), along with two known compounds were isolated from the mushroom Hericium coralloides. Their benzofuranone and isoindolinone structures were elucidated by spectral methods. All corallocins induced nerve growth factor and/or brain-derived neurotrophic factor expression in human 1321N1 astrocytes. Furthermore, corallocin B showed antiproliferative activity against HUVEC and human cancer cell lines MCF-7 and KB-3-1.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Wittstein","given":"Kathrin","literal":""},{"family":"Wittstein","given":"Kathrin","literal":""},{"family":"Rascher","given":"Monique","literal":""},{"family":"Rascher","given":"Monique","literal":""},{"family":"Rupcic","given":"Zeljka","literal":""},{"family":"Rupcic","given":"Zeljka","literal":""},{"family":"Löwen","given":"Eduard","literal":""},{"family":"Löwen","given":"Eduard","literal":""},{"family":"Winter","given":"Barbara","literal":""},{"family":"Winter","given":"Barbara","literal":""},{"family":"Köster","given":"Reinhard W.","literal":""},{"family":"Köster","given":"Reinhard W.","literal":""},{"family":"Stadler","given":"Marc","literal":""},{"family":"Stadler","given":"Marc","literal":""}],"citation-key":"wittstein_corallocins_2016","year":"2016","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Corallocins A-C, Nerve Growth and Brain-Deri